# Creature Stat Block Lookup

When reading or running any adventure in this project, every bolded creature name
is a **clickable link** to its stat block file. The link format is:

```
[**creature name**](statblocks/SOURCE/Creature Name.md)
```

## When to Read a Stat Block

Before describing an encounter or combat involving a creature, **always read its
stat block file** to get accurate HP, AC, attacks, abilities, and special traits.

Do not rely on memory for creature stats — always fetch the file.

## Finding a Creature

1. **Follow the link** in the adventure text — every creature name is already linked.
2. **Use the index** if you need to look one up directly: [`statblocks/index.md`](../../statblocks/index.md)
3. **Path pattern** if you know the name and source: `statblocks/{SOURCE}/{Name}.md`

